    "body": "### Problem\n\nlibvterm is missing some features and moving too slowly.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEvaluate if libghostty ~~or libvaxis~~ can replace libvterm.\n\n- full support (including scrollback) for reflow. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/30117\n\nlibvaxis is more like a \"TUI sdk\" for building TUI apps. It could perhaps replace parts of `tui.c`, and [hopefully unibilium](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/31989). Although libvaxis doesn't read terminfo, we may not need that anyway.\n\n### Reference\n\n- https://libghostty.tip.ghostty.org (API reference)\n- https://github.com/ghostty-org/ghostling\n    - example CMake: https://github.com/ghostty-org/ghostty/pull/11700",
