            "body": "I'm going to add some commentary from the above (since I generated it) that there's some bullshit too. I had a meeting to run to for 30 minutes and I use opportunities like that to do some background research cause I wouldn't be able to anyways. Then use it as a \"warm start\" when I get back to work. I don't take it as gospel.\n\nIt did identify some very obvious general gaps (not Neovim-specific), such as setting colors, parser hooks, etc. So, onwards!",
