        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "As a new neovim convert, I have to lodge a complaint that ghostty will not compile on older macOS systems due to rapidly changing Swift and Metal APIs. At the risk of sounding like *old man yells at cloud* I personally have reasons to be using older systems, and therefore have no problem _not_ having access to Ghostty the hawt new terminal emulator. However if my editor of choice relies on a thing that requires me to update my macOS, I must complain. For context, Ghostty requires macOS 13+ to even do a test build. Thanks for listening to my rant, command line tools should not have dependencies on graphical frontends IMO, no matter how sophisticated.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-06T21:56:03Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/33155#issuecomment-4195229776",
