        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@vaporstack The point is to switch the parser of ANSI sequences, the logic responsible for rendering and reflowing text and such, from libvterm to logic from libghostty. I personally doubt this will require much use of system-specific APIs. You can check out the code that is currently responsible for this here: <https://github.com/neovim/neovim/tree/master/src/nvim/vterm>.",
