        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@vaporstack You're confusing Ghostty with libghostty. libghostty has no Swift, no Metal. It works on significantly older Apple platforms as well as a significantly broader set of platforms (such as Windows, but many others). libghostty has no dependencies other than libc (if you disable our SIMD support, it doesn't even depend on libc and is fully freestanding). ",
